# NestJS Conventions

## Module Structure
```
module/
├── module.controller.ts
├── module.service.ts
├── module.module.ts
├── dto/
│   └── *.dto.ts
└── interfaces/
    └── *.interface.ts
```

## Patterns
- DTOs use class-validator (`@IsString`, `@IsEmail`, `@IsNotEmpty`, `@MaxLength(255)`)
- Services throw NestJS HTTP exceptions (`NotFoundException`, `ConflictException`, `UnauthorizedException`)
- Auth guards: `JwtAuthGuard` (any authenticated), `RolesGuard` + `@Roles('ADMIN')` (admin only)
- `@CurrentUser()` decorator extracts user from request (set by JwtStrategy)
- Global `ValidationPipe({ whitelist: true, forbidNonWhitelisted: true, transform: true })`
- Logging via Winston (NOT console.log except in services without DI)
